&lt;Helikopter Service A/S>, Norway'sbiggest helicopter operator, will assemble 18 Bell 412 SPhelicopters for Norwegian Defence under license from &lt;BellHelicopters Textron> of the U.S., The company said.    The 18 medium-range helicopters, worth 540 mln crowns, willbe assembled at the company's facilities at Sola airport inStavanger. Helikopter Service technical director Trygve Eidemsaid the 25-mln crown assembly contract will help the companydiversify its operations. Helikopter Service's main income isfrom chartered flights between Norway's North Sea oil fieldsand mainland heliports. REUTER&#3;